<HL>
   Business Brief -- May Department Stores Co.:
   St. Louis Concern's Profit
   Rose 27% in First Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MA
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)
</IN>
<LP>
   May Department Stores Co. said profit rose nearly 27% in
the fiscal first quarter.
   The St. Louis retailer reported net income of $80 million,
or 58 cents a share, compared with $63 million, or 45 cents a
share, a year earlier. The year-ago figure includes a loss of
$1 million, or one cent a share, on the company's
discontinued discount store operations.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   May Chairman David C. Farrell said the results indicate
that the company "is off to a good start for 1990." Sales in
the quarter ended May 5 rose to $2.19 billion from $2.05
billion.
</TEXT>
